{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Ensure Mobile Responsiveness for Card and Column Components\n\nFix layout issues affecting card items and columnar elements on mobile devices, specifically addressing contact cards not displaying at full width.\n\nRequirements:\n- Audit all card components across the application to identify mobile layout issues\n- Ensure contact cards render at full width (100%) on mobile breakpoints\n- Verify columnar layouts stack vertically on mobile screens\n- Check that padding and margins are appropriate for mobile viewports\n- Test card content (text, images, buttons) scales correctly without overflow\n- Apply consistent mobile breakpoint behavior (typically < 768px)\n- Ensure touch targets meet minimum size requirements (44x44px)\n- Test across multiple mobile device sizes (small phones 320px to tablets 768px)\n- Verify no horizontal scrolling occurs on mobile views\n\nEdge Cases to Consider:\n- Cards with varying content lengths\n- Cards containing images or icons\n- Nested card components\n- Grid or flexbox layouts containing cards\n- Cards within containers that have their own width constraints",
